üîπ BASIC LEVEL MCQs (10)
1. SOX was introduced primarily to:
A. Improve cybersecurity tools
B. Prevent corporate fraud
C. Standardize IT services
D. Replace ISO standards

2. SOX mainly focuses on controls related to:
A. Network security
B. Financial reporting
C. Incident response
D. Data encryption

3. SOC reports are issued by:
A. Internal IT teams
B. Independent auditors
C. Regulators
D. Customers

4. SOC reports are MOST relevant for:
A. Manufacturing firms
B. Service organizations
C. Law enforcement
D. Individuals

5. Which SOC report focuses on internal controls over financial reporting?
A. SOC 1
B. SOC 2
C. SOC 3
D. SOC Type III

6. SOX compliance requires management to:
A. Ignore IT controls
B. Assess effectiveness of internal controls
C. Eliminate audits
D. Avoid documentation

7. COBIT primarily provides guidance for:
A. IT governance and management
B. Network design
C. Incident handling
D. Coding standards

8. COBIT is MOST commonly used by:
A. Developers
B. IT auditors and management
C. End users
D. Hackers

9. ITIL mainly focuses on:
A. IT governance
B. IT service management
C. Compliance laws
D. Financial controls

10. COBIT and ITIL are best described as:
A. Legal regulations
B. Complementary frameworks
C. Competing laws
D. Security tools

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE LEVEL MCQs (10)
