A. Processes
B. Organizational structures
C. Information
D. Malware signatures

17. COBIT helps organizations to:
A. Write code
B. Align IT goals with business goals
C. Eliminate audits
D. Replace ISO

18. ITIL processes are primarily designed to:
A. Govern IT investments
B. Deliver and support IT services
C. Conduct compliance audits
D. Perform risk assessment

19. COBIT is considered more suitable than ITIL for:
A. Service desk operations
B. Governance and control objectives
C. Incident ticketing
D. Change scheduling

20. SOC 2 Type II reports differ from Type I because they:
A. Cover fewer controls
B. Test operating effectiveness over time
C. Are unaudited
D. Are public

